                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">898.24/548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-30T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >March 30, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 30—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>227. Reference Embassy’s telegram 216, March 28, 10 a.m.<note n="49"
                        xml:id="d718fn49">Not printed.</note> The Embassy learns from an informed
                    Chinese source that Sun Fo’s<note n="50" xml:id="d718fn50">President of the
                        Chinese Legislative Yuan.</note> mission to Moscow is to plead with
                        Stalin<note n="51" xml:id="d718fn51">Josif V. Stalin, Secretary General of
                        the Communist Party in the Soviet Union.</note> with whom he is on good
                    terms for the granting of additional Russian support to China in the form of
                    arms and munitions, and especially military aircraft the maintenance of the
                    average number of which the Chinese authorities hope to increase from a present
                    total of 200 to 500 available planes. The same source [apparent omission] Sun is
                    [to?] proceed in about 2 weeks to Paris and London for discussions along similar
                    lines with French and British officials.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
